3/19/14

Some useful commands for doing reconnaissance are:
ping sweep
nmap (port scanning)
airmon; tcpdump; wireshanck (network sniffing)
netcat


ACK SYN-ACK ACK

This above piece is a primary conversation that happens between computers before packets are sent, in which the sender requests permission to send.
A port scan may be used to check what is listening on the port, even what version or the OS running.
Milworm and metasploit have lists of known exploits and weaknesses of systems.

Triad of defensive actions:
1) patch updates
2) malware protection
3) firewall

Threat avoidance
